Gunmen have reportedly killed one person in an attack in Sabon Gari Local Government Area of Kaduna State. The victim identified as Yarima Mohammed of Kufena village Wusasa was killed when he resisted the gunmen in the process of being abducted. The Police in Kaduna State who confirmed the attack disclosed this in a statement. According to the Spokesman of the Command, Mohammed Jalige, the bandits dressed in military uniforms and armed with sophisticated weapons invaded Gabari community, Samaru area of Sabon Gari, and started shooting sporadically, and in the process whisked four persons away into the forest. On getting the information, the command immediately mobilized operational assets alongside men of Operation Puff Adder II and local vigilantes; who courageously laid ambush on the banditsâ€™ expected route and successfully rescued two people that were kidnapped by the bandits.